						h2.section-title The Client
						p Fuigo's goal is to help interior designers optimize their business practices.
					.project-section.mbl
						h2.section-title The Problem
						p Interior designers are running into disconnects by using several different programs to conduct their business. Having several different programs to keep track of causes them to feel scattered and less prepared.
					.project-section.mbl
						h2.section-title The Solution
						p Pivotal and Fuigo developed a web application that streamlined the budgeting, quoting, and purchasing workflow for interior designers. As a result, interior designers could spend more time on design while (also) feeling confident about executing proper business practices.
					.project-section.mbl
						h2.section-title My Role
						p As lead product designer, I worked collaboratively with the client, engineers, and product manager. I conducted research/experiments, prioritized solutions, wireframed/prototyped and created live styleguides and marketing materials. Throughout the project, I taught the client how and when to use these agile, lean, and user centered design techniques.
