						h2.section-title Research & Prototyping
						p Fuigo came to us with a ton of industry knowledge and a roster of interior designers for us to interview. We conducted over 15 interviews, went on-site with designers, and balanced user feedback with Fuigo's business goals.
				.col-md-6
					.project-section.mbl
						h2.section-title What we learned:
						ul.default-ul
							li Designers are looking for a well organized way of documenting their budget and purchasing costs per project. Currently this is being done across disconnected applications.
							li Designers are looking for guided workflows to teach them better business practices. 
							li Designers want to put clients at ease by increasing communication.
				.col-md-6
					.project-section.mbl
						p With these insights in mind, we began sketching and prototyping solutions. We initially focused on making it simple for an interior designer to budget complicated items in large projects. We also worked on generating well-designed documents to share with clients. We quickly put those prototypes back in the hands of designers for validation and feedback.
				.col-md-12
